@Node Erklärung
This programm allows ou to have an online manual in your shell.

                                  Usage:
                               man {Command}

What does it do? It is very easy: the programm is looking in s: or in ram:
for the file "manual.txt" looks for the command you are searching for and
shows you its explanation.
@Endnode
@Node Format
                          Format of "manual.txt":

               .-------------------------------------------.
               | @Command                                  |
               |                                           |
               | 	Explanation                         |
               | 	Explanation                         |
               | 	Explanation                         |
               | 	and so on                           |
               | @Next Command                             |
               |                                           |
               | 	Explanation                         |
               | 	Explanation                         |
               |	Explanation                         |
               | 	and so on                           |
               | @Next Command                             |
               |                                           |
               | 	Explanation                         |
               | 	Explanation                         |
               |	Explanation                         |
               | 	and so on                           |
               | @                                         |
               `-------------------------------------------´
                 ^
                 `- The last "@" is not really important.

                            It is very easy no?
@Endnode
