@Endnode
@Node Bemerkung
Speed remark: if I boot without the startup-sequence I have another
speedgain of 6% or an overall speedgain of 26%. This means that other
Programms running in the background also want to be deserved by the
processor, so that the programm would run faster under a 68060 than under
my 68030 or even flying in comparison with a A500 without fast-ram. So if
you want to keep the programm fast, try to kickout the most explanations as
possible: 
less explanations -> more speed, shorter explanations -> more speed
last hint: put all explanations that you use often in the front of the
file, so that they could be found faster, in the manual.txt in the archive
it makes a difference of 5 secs on my machine if a explanation can be found
at the beginning or at the end of manual.txt.
@Endnode
